table. REJECTION-GATE: Agentic was considered but rejected under the assumption that the summary should be built from the collected findings list, not re-generated independently — a design that makes the invariant verifiable without a real model. If implementation uses independent LLM generation for both, the level should be raised to Agentic.","test_description":"Stub the LLM to return a fixed list of N findings (each with file, line, message). Run the full comment-posting and summary-generation pipeline against a mocked GitHub API spy. After the run, collect all inline comment calls and the summary comment call from the spy. Assert that every finding mentioned in the summary body has a corresponding inline comment call with matching location and content — and that no extra findings appear in the summary.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"The test_description is consistent with Integration, but note: if the actual implementation has the LLM generate the summary independently (not from collected findings), the minimum level rises to Agentic.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.5,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.28,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP: The behavior explicitly names three sequential steps that must all complete correctly: (1) read the diff from a real PR, (2) post inline comments, (3) post the summary comment. Each step depends on the output of the previous. REAL-INFRA: 'real pull request' means real GitHub API calls — System-level at minimum. LLM-DEP: The review step between reading the diff and posting comments involves a real LLM call — Agentic at minimum. Combining real sequential agentic inference with real external API I/O across multiple steps makes this Workflow. REJECTION-GATE: System was 